5-87:4.2.2 Performance Measures We use three common metrics to assess prediction accuracy of information markets and opinion pools .
5-88:These measures have been used by Servan Schreiber et .
5-89:al [36] in evaluating the prediction accuracy of information markets. .
6 Absolute Error = Prob Lose, :
6-1:where Prob Lose is the probability assigned to the eventual losing team .
6-2:Absolute error simply measures the difference between a perfect prediction (1 for winning team) and the actual prediction .
6-3:A prediction with lower absolute error is more accurate .
6-4:) .
6-5:Quadratic score is the scoring function that is used in the ProbabilityFootball contest .
6-6:It is a linear transformation of squared error, Prob Lose2 , which is one of the mostly used metrics in evaluating forecasting accuracy .
6-7:Quadratic score can be negative .
6-8:A prediction with higher quadratic score is more accurate. .
7 Logarithmic Score = log(Prob W in), :
7-1:where Prob W in is the probability assigned to the eventual winning team .
7-2:The logarithmic score, like the quadratic score, is a proper scoring rule .
7-3:A prediction with higher (less negative) logarithmic score is more accurate. .
8 EMPIRICAL RESULTS :
8-1:5.1 Performance of Opinion Pools Depending on how many opinions are used, there can be numerous different opinion pools .
8-2:We first examine the effect of number of opinions on prediction accuracy by forming opinion pools with the number of expert opinions varying from 1 to 960 .
8-3:In the ProbabilityFootball Competition, not all 1966 registered participants provide their probability assessments for every game .
8-4:960 is the smallest number of participants for all games .
8-5:For each game, we sort experts according to their accumulated quadratic score in previous weeks .
8-6:Predictions of the best performing n participants are picked to form an opinion pool with n experts .
8-7:Figure 1 shows the prediction accuracy of LinOP and LogOP in terms of mean values of the three performance measures across all 210 games .
