8-15:But the curves (including the points with all experts) for mean quadratic score, and mean logarithmic score have slight bell shapes, which represent a decrease in prediction accuracy when the number of experts is very large .
8-16:The curves for mean absolute error, on the other hand, show a consistent increase of accuracy .
8-17:The first and second trend above imply that when using LinOP, the simplest way, which has good prediction accuracy, is to average the opinions of all experts .
